  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> to a baking tray and put the tray in the  oven to heat up</p><p>Cut the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Once the oil is hot, add the <strong>sweet potato</strong> <strong>chips</strong> with the <strong>dried sage</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then give everything a good mix up and cook for 20-22 min or until the chips are golden – these are your <strong>sage sweet potato chips</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-beef-meatball-christmas-sarnie/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>beef mince</strong>,<strong> grated ginger</strong>,<strong> soy sauce </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>in a bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> meatball mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-beef-meatball-christmas-sarnie/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>meatball mix</strong> into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> and shape them into meatballs</p><p>Add the <strong>beef</strong> <strong>meatballs</strong> to a separate baking tray (use baking paper to avoid mess!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-14 min or until cooked through</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-beef-meatball-christmas-sarnie/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and peel the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and <strong>parsnip<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot and parsnip ribbons – these are your <strong>root veg ribbons</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-beef-meatball-christmas-sarnie/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>root veg ribbons</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>rice vinegar</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar </strong>and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>pickled root veg ribbons</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-beef-meatball-christmas-sarnie/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Wash, then remove 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> <strong>outer</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from the<strong> gem lettuce</strong> and set aside, then shred the <strong>inner core</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-beef-meatball-christmas-sarnie/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>ciabattas</strong> in half</p><p>Add the<strong> ciabattas halves</strong> to the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p><p>Spread the <strong>warmed ciabatta halves</strong> with the <strong>cranberry sauce</strong> and <strong>mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-beef-meatball-christmas-sarnie/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To build, fill each <strong>ciabatta</strong> with a <strong>lettuce leaf</strong>, <strong>pickled root veg ribbons </strong>(save the pickling liquid!),<strong> beef meatballs </strong>and a sprinkling of the <strong>chopped coriander </strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> Vietnamese beef meatball Christmas sarnie </strong>with the<strong> sage sweet potato chips </strong>and the<strong> shredded lettuce </strong>to the side</p><p>Top the chips<strong> </strong>with the<strong> sliced spring onion </strong>and drizzle a little <strong>olive oil </strong>and the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>pickling liquid </strong>over the lettuce</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
